26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_mc_gf100.c,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:34 riastradh Exp $");

29#include "priv.h"
30
31const struct nvkm_mc_intr
32gf100_mc_intr[] = {
33 { 0x04000000, NVKM_ENGINE_DISP }, /* DISP first, so pageflip timestamps work. */
34 { 0x00000001, NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP },
35 { 0x00000020, NVKM_ENGINE_CE0 },
36 { 0x00000040, NVKM_ENGINE_CE1 },
37 { 0x00000080, NVKM_ENGINE_CE2 },
38 { 0x00000100, NVKM_ENGINE_FIFO },
39 { 0x00001000, NVKM_ENGINE_GR },
40 { 0x00002000, NVKM_SUBDEV_FB },
41 { 0x00008000, NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD },
42 { 0x00040000, NVKM_SUBDEV_THERM },
43 { 0x00020000, NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC },
44 { 0x00100000, NVKM_SUBDEV_TIMER },
45 { 0x00200000, NVKM_SUBDEV_GPIO }, /* PMGR->GPIO */
46 { 0x00200000, NVKM_SUBDEV_I2C }, /* PMGR->I2C/AUX */
47 { 0x01000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_PMU },
48 { 0x02000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_LTC },
49 { 0x08000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_FB },
50 { 0x10000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_BUS },
51 { 0x40000000, NVKM_SUBDEV_IBUS },
52 { 0x80000000, NVKM_ENGINE_SW },
53 {},
54};
55
56void
57gf100_mc_intr_unarm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
58{
59 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
60 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000140, 0x00000000);
61 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000144, 0x00000000);
62 nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000140);
63}
64
65void
66gf100_mc_intr_rearm(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
67{
68 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
69 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000140, 0x00000001);
70 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x000144, 0x00000001);
71}
72
73u32
74gf100_mc_intr_mask(struct nvkm_mc *mc)
75{
76 struct nvkm_device *device = mc->subdev.device;
77 u32 intr0 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000100);
78 u32 intr1 = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x000104);
79 return intr0 | intr1;
80}
81
82void
83gf100_mc_unk260(struct nvkm_mc *mc, u32 data)
84{
85 nvkm_wr32(mc->subdev.device, 0x000260, data);
86}
87
88static const struct nvkm_mc_func
89gf100_mc = {
90 .init = nv50_mc_init,
91 .intr = gf100_mc_intr,
92 .intr_unarm = gf100_mc_intr_unarm,
93 .intr_rearm = gf100_mc_intr_rearm,
94 .intr_mask = gf100_mc_intr_mask,
95 .unk260 = gf100_mc_unk260,
96};
97
98int
99gf100_mc_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_mc **pmc)
100{
101 return nvkm_mc_new_(&gf100_mc, device, index, pmc);
102}
